Self-acclaimed ‘wahala singer’ Portable has clapped back at persons trolling him over his constant social media posts. The fast-rising street artiste, in a video shared on his Instagram page while warning, hurled curses at people telling him to utilise social media moderately by lessening his social posts. He also took a swipe at those who query his data usage, as he reminded them that they didn’t purchase his phone or data adding, his iPhone 13 will buy their cars. The “Zazu” crooner also used the opportunity to appreciate his loyal fans and lovers for supporting his hustle.   Babies have no conscience – Williams Uchemba     Igboho fate’s at Beninoise prison hangs in balance     Asa releases fifth album, features Wizkid, Amaarae, others   He said: ““Are you kidding me? Did you buy data for me? You’re just talking to me anyhow…reduce your post. Did you by the phone for me? “Do you know the phone I’m using? It’s an iPhone 13 o! Do you know how much it’s sold? It can buy your car. Are you mad? You’re commenting under my post, saying all sorts of rubbish. “Do you know who will help you? You’re talking to me indiscriminately. I am a big man, talk to me. If you talk to me anyhow, I’ll eliminate you. Are you mad or something? “Thanks to those that show me love. All my fans, they know me.”